text:
$$
\text{Basic earnings per share (₹)} = \frac{\text{Restated Profit After Tax attributable to Equity Shareholders}}{\text{Weighted Average Number of Equity Shares outstanding}}
$$

$$
\text{Diluted earnings per share (₹)} = \frac{\text{Restated Profit After Tax attributable to Equity Shareholders}}{\text{Weighted Average Number of Equity Shares adjusted for effect of all diluted potential equity shares}}
$$

$$
\text{Price to Earnings Ratio(P/E)} = \frac{\text{Issue Price}}{\text{Restated Adjusted Earnings Per Share}}
$$
